WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:58.120
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:15.040
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:45.880
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.920
Tin Plate Wapol

24
00:01:54.940 --> 00:02:00.430
Guys! Someday, I will go to Elbaph!
To the village of warriors!

25
00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:01.890
Yeah! Okay!

26
00:02:02.330 --> 00:02:06.260
♪ Gi-Gi-Giants! Gia-Giants! ♪

27
00:02:06.260 --> 00:02:10.100
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph-baph! ♪

28
00:02:10.100 --> 00:02:13.950
♪ Everyone's huge
'cause they're giants! ♪

29
00:02:13.950 --> 00:02:17.500
♪ They're huge! They're huge!
They're huge! ♪

30
00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:19.720
They sure are lively today...

31
00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:29.650
Suddenly, I'm pretty worn out
after all that's happened...

32
00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:33.670
Vivi... could you keep an eye
on the needle for me?

33
00:02:33.670 --> 00:02:34.420
Sure.

34
00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:43.260
Now you can finally...
return to Alabasta.

35
00:02:43.260 --> 00:02:48.310
That is, assuming we can
avoid trouble along the way.

36
00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:52.010
Yes. It's time I returned!

37
00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:54.860
After all, I am...

38
00:02:54.860 --> 00:02:58.320
...the only one who can
save the kingdom, Princess!

39
00:02:58.320 --> 00:03:03.570
The king—your father—no longer
holds sway over his people.

40
00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:07.740
Our only hope to stem
the tide of rebellion is for the country

41
00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:10.290
to hear the truth directly from you.

42
00:03:11.050 --> 00:03:14.330
So, no matter the cost,
you must not die!

43
00:03:14.330 --> 00:03:17.590
If it means you survive,
then sacrifice those closest to you

44
00:03:17.590 --> 00:03:19.700
or betray them to your enemies!

45
00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:21.130
It will be agony!

46
00:03:21.900 --> 00:03:25.600
Princess Vivi! Are you
resolved to stay alive?

47
00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:31.480
I will stay alive
and return to Alabasta.

48
00:03:39.460 --> 00:03:42.490
No need to push
yourself so hard, Vivi.

49
00:03:44.100 --> 00:03:44.990
You have me!

50
00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:49.860
Today's sweets will put you
right at ease. Petit fours?

51
00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:52.210
And to drink, would you
like coffee or tea?

52
00:03:53.580 --> 00:03:54.670
Sanji!

53
00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:00.920
Yours is in the kitchen!

54
00:04:00.920 --> 00:04:03.090
– Alright!
– Alright!

55
00:04:03.990 --> 00:04:05.760
I got there first!

56
00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:07.510
2,603...

57
00:04:08.600 --> 00:04:09.890
2,604...

58
00:04:10.830 --> 00:04:11.730
2,605...

59
00:04:13.330 --> 00:04:14.860
2,606...!

60
00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:21.000
If only I'd been able
to cut through that wax...

61
00:04:22.730 --> 00:04:25.090
we would've escaped so much sooner.

62
00:04:28.130 --> 00:04:29.290
I'm weak...

63
00:04:30.910 --> 00:04:33.250
I need to get stronger...

64
00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:38.310
and get to where I can
cut through stuff like that with ease!

65
00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:46.220
Sandy Island
Kingdom of Alabasta

66
00:04:46.220 --> 00:04:51.180
Mr. 2 Bon Kurei!
The Swanda is ready to set sail!

67
00:04:52.210 --> 00:04:56.270
Okay, okay! Dial it down a notch!

68
00:04:56.270 --> 00:05:00.210
Honestly! What does any of this
have to do with me?!

69
00:05:00.210 --> 00:05:03.110
Mr. 3 is a waste of space!
You guys go finish him off!

70
00:05:03.460 --> 00:05:04.820
W-We can't!

71
00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:07.530
Even all of us together
wouldn't stand a chance!

72
00:05:07.530 --> 00:05:09.950
P-Please! It's the boss' orders!

73
00:05:10.240 --> 00:05:12.160
Un, deux, trois...

74
00:05:13.330 --> 00:05:17.960
"Bon Kurei"

75
00:05:13.350 --> 00:05:15.490
What's "four" again?

76
00:05:19.280 --> 00:05:21.880
Zero baby is so high maintenance...

77
00:05:27.420 --> 00:05:30.330
Vivi... Sorry. I think I'm gonna...

78
00:05:38.740 --> 00:05:39.740
go lie down.

79
00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:42.790
No problem, Nami!

80
00:05:42.790 --> 00:05:44.620
I'll keep an eye on our heading.

81
00:05:44.620 --> 00:05:46.490
You should get some rest.

82
00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:53.200
Are you all right?!

83
00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:55.580
Everyone, come here! It's urgent!

84
00:05:57.570 --> 00:05:59.470
Huh? What's up, Vivi?

85
00:05:59.470 --> 00:06:01.130
Nami has a terrible fever!

86
00:06:01.130 --> 00:06:03.340
Say what?! Nami has a what?!

87
00:06:19.810 --> 00:06:24.360
Is Nami gonna die? Is she, Vivi?

88
00:06:33.380 --> 00:06:35.240
It's most likely the climate.

89
00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:39.210
Illness caused by abnormal weather
is a well-known obstacle

90
00:06:39.210 --> 00:06:40.880
for those new to the Grand Line.

91
00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:48.100
There are countless stories
of the toughest, most infamous pirates

92
00:06:48.100 --> 00:06:49.550
suddenly dying from it.

93
00:06:50.350 --> 00:06:53.430
If left untreated,
even the slightest chill can be fatal.

94
00:06:54.810 --> 00:06:57.060
Nami!

95
00:06:57.690 --> 00:07:01.480
Does someone on the ship have
any kind of medical training?

96
00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:11.500
Well, she'll feel better once
she eats some meat! Right, Sanji?

97
00:07:12.230 --> 00:07:16.110
Y'know, I can think of a few meals
meant to nurse sick people.

98
00:07:16.110 --> 00:07:20.040
But nursing isn't my expertise,
so there's no telling if it would help.

99
00:07:21.030 --> 00:07:23.210
Even so, I put 100 times more care

100
00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:28.330
into Nami and Vivi's meals
than I do yours.

101
00:07:29.390 --> 00:07:33.230
To balance their diet, I only serve them
fresh meat and vegetables.

102
00:07:33.230 --> 00:07:36.260
And I give all the rotting stuff...
to you guys.

103
00:07:36.260 --> 00:07:37.210
Hey, now!

104
00:07:37.210 --> 00:07:39.060
It tastes great, though!

105
00:07:40.850 --> 00:07:44.490
My point is, as long as
I'm this ship's cook,

106
00:07:44.490 --> 00:07:48.530
I will always guarantee
you get a balanced diet.

107
00:07:49.190 --> 00:07:53.200
But sick people
require specific meals.

108
00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:56.270
What does she need,
and for which symptoms?

109
00:07:56.270 --> 00:07:58.370
I can't make that call.

110
00:07:58.620 --> 00:08:01.000
Then feed her everything!

111
00:08:01.290 --> 00:08:05.460
Going overboard like that
is bound to make her sicker!

112
00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:10.050
I-It's at 40 degrees?!
Her fever's gone up!

113
00:08:10.770 --> 00:08:13.660
There are doctors in Alabasta, right?!

114
00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:15.260
How long till we arrive, Vivi?

115
00:08:16.530 --> 00:08:20.020
A week maybe,
but it might be too late by then.

116
00:08:20.650 --> 00:08:22.690
Is being sick that bad?

117
00:08:22.690 --> 00:08:25.400
Dunno. Never been sick.

118
00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:28.020
Who in the world are you guys?!

119
00:08:28.770 --> 00:08:30.250
Of course it's bad!

120
00:08:30.250 --> 00:08:33.490
Fevers of 40 degrees
don't happen every day!

121
00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:37.200
Her life may very well be at stake.

122
00:08:38.410 --> 00:08:44.100
– Nami's gonna die?!
– Don't die, Nami!

123
00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:45.880
Settle down! Be quiet!

124
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:49.460
Let's find a doctor to help Nami!

125
00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:52.060
Okay! Just calm down!

126
00:08:52.060 --> 00:08:53.600
You'll make her worse!

127
00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:54.550
No...

128
00:08:57.600 --> 00:08:58.510
No...

129
00:09:00.010 --> 00:09:01.110
Nami?

130
00:09:01.110 --> 00:09:02.770
Oh! She's all better!

131
00:09:02.770 --> 00:09:03.520
Get real!

132
00:09:05.570 --> 00:09:09.860
In my desk drawer...
there's a newspaper.

133
00:09:14.640 --> 00:09:17.410
No change in course...

134
00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:20.120
N-No!

135
00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:21.990
This can't be!

136
00:09:21.990 --> 00:09:24.000
Hey. What is it?

137
00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:26.210
Is it about Alabasta, Vivi?

138
00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:31.550
My kingdom just saw 300,000 of
the Royal Army defect to the Rebellion.

139
00:09:34.130 --> 00:09:37.580
It all started as a cold war

140
00:09:37.580 --> 00:09:41.340
with the 600,000 Royal Army soldiers
deterring the 400,000 rebels.

141
00:09:41.340 --> 00:09:43.220
But this changes everything!

142
00:09:45.020 --> 00:09:49.160
The tensions in Alabasta are
only going to intensify from here on.

143
00:09:49.530 --> 00:09:51.570
That paper's from three days ago.

144
00:09:52.500 --> 00:09:56.890
I'm sorry...
We can only go so fast.

145
00:09:56.890 --> 00:09:59.030
I thought if you saw this
you'd only worry...

146
00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:01.530
Understand, Luffy?

147
00:10:02.920 --> 00:10:05.180
Things look pretty bad!

148
00:10:05.180 --> 00:10:07.140
Whew, you got the gist of it.

149
00:10:07.140 --> 00:10:09.500
But you still need to see a doctor!

150
00:10:09.920 --> 00:10:12.840
I'm fine... That thermometer
must be broken.

151
00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:15.390
Nobody gets
a temperature of 40 degrees...

152
00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:18.010
It's most likely sunstroke.

153
00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:21.190
I don't need a doctor.
I'll get better on my own.

154
00:10:22.110 --> 00:10:25.350
For now, let's head
straight for Alabasta as planned!

155
00:10:27.490 --> 00:10:29.690
Thanks for worrying about me.

156
00:10:35.850 --> 00:10:37.750
Oh! She's better now?

157
00:10:38.450 --> 00:10:39.990
Don't be stupid. It's just a front.

158
00:10:50.940 --> 00:10:54.790
At this rate, blood will flow
through the kingdom's streets.

159
00:10:54.790 --> 00:10:55.960
It'll be an all-out war.

160
00:10:56.440 --> 00:11:00.570
If I don't prevent that,
the Kingdom of Alabasta will be finished.

161
00:11:01.570 --> 00:11:03.930
Crocodile will take over!

162
00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:07.770
It's not enough...
to simply get back alive!

163
00:11:07.770 --> 00:11:09.390
I must expedite my return!

164
00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:14.920
A moment wasted means a million citizens
will senselessly kill each other!

165
00:11:14.920 --> 00:11:17.530
There's a million people?!

166
00:11:17.530 --> 00:11:20.990
What an immense burden
you're carrying, Vivi.

167
00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:37.840
C'mon! Were you even
paying attention up here?!

168
00:11:37.840 --> 00:11:40.830
Whad'ya mean?
The ship's going straight.

169
00:11:40.830 --> 00:11:42.770
Yeah, straight at a right angle!

170
00:11:43.420 --> 00:11:45.240
You need to watch the needle!

171
00:11:45.240 --> 00:11:48.930
That wasn't necessary.
I was watching that big cloud there.

172
00:11:48.930 --> 00:11:51.390
Clouds move and change shape!

173
00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:54.450
Oh, man, my head's killing me...

174
00:11:54.450 --> 00:11:57.070
So then leave this to me
and go to bed!

175
00:11:57.070 --> 00:12:00.010
I'm here because
I can't leave this to you!

176
00:12:02.070 --> 00:12:03.820
The air's different.

177
00:12:03.820 --> 00:12:07.090
The air? The weather's been
nice this whole time.

178
00:12:07.090 --> 00:12:09.290
Forget it! Just get the others!

179
00:12:09.290 --> 00:12:12.000
Hey! Get out here, you guys!
We've got work to do!

180
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:14.080
What?

181
00:12:15.280 --> 00:12:19.170
Huh? Hard to feel motivated
when it's you giving the orders.

182
00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:21.320
Just shut up and move!

183
00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:23.630
Hoist the sails
and catch the wind aport!

184
00:12:24.010 --> 00:12:25.760
Everything okay, Nami?

185
00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:27.850
The waves are quiet,
and the weather's nice.

186
00:12:29.480 --> 00:12:30.640
The wind...

187
00:12:31.660 --> 00:12:32.690
The wind?

188
00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:36.450
The wind is picking up
and heading directly toward us.

189
00:12:36.450 --> 00:12:37.900
I think th–

190
00:12:37.900 --> 00:12:38.870
What?

191
00:12:39.790 --> 00:12:40.690
Hot!

192
00:12:40.690 --> 00:12:43.820
You're burning up! Yeah,
stay inside until we find a doctor!

193
00:12:43.820 --> 00:12:45.520
Mind your own business!

194
00:12:45.520 --> 00:12:47.340
This is my normal temperature!

195
00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:49.080
Quit being dumb and man the ropes!

196
00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:55.420
Nami, I get that this is
for Vivi's sake, but if you overdo it...

197
00:12:55.840 --> 00:12:57.630
I told you, I'm fine!

198
00:13:02.920 --> 00:13:05.300
C'mon, Nami! You really ought to–

199
00:13:05.510 --> 00:13:07.800
Just hurry it up and turn the ship!

200
00:13:15.590 --> 00:13:16.400
But...

201
00:13:17.670 --> 00:13:19.100
what could it be?

202
00:13:19.910 --> 00:13:22.900
This is a bit different from a storm.

203
00:13:49.770 --> 00:13:52.450
I need to hurry... back to Alabasta.

204
00:13:56.780 --> 00:13:58.150
Everyone, I need a favor!

205
00:14:00.070 --> 00:14:04.010
As a passenger on your ship,
I know I have no right to ask this,

206
00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:07.400
but my homeland is
on the brink of disaster.

207
00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:09.160
So we need to expedite our trip!

208
00:14:09.490 --> 00:14:11.610
We can't waste even a single minute!

209
00:14:11.610 --> 00:14:15.960
You must take me to Alabasta
at this ship's top speed!

210
00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:20.000
Of course!
That's what we promised!

211
00:14:23.880 --> 00:14:27.590
So let's find an island
with a doctor right away!

212
00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:32.730
The sooner we cure Nami,
the sooner we get to Alabasta!

213
00:14:32.730 --> 00:14:35.140
That's this ship's top speed, right?!

214
00:14:35.950 --> 00:14:38.640
Yeah! We can't go
any faster than that!

215
00:14:39.310 --> 00:14:40.570
Are you sure?

216
00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:44.530
Shouldn't a princess be more worried
about her one million citizens?

217
00:14:45.310 --> 00:14:48.950
You're right! All the more reason
to hurry and cure Nami!

218
00:14:49.630 --> 00:14:51.410
Well said, Vivi!

219
00:14:51.410 --> 00:14:52.910
I've fallen for you all over again!

220
00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:54.950
You've got spirit.

221
00:14:55.740 --> 00:14:57.260
Thanks...

222
00:14:57.260 --> 00:14:59.720
Don't overexert yourself, Nami!

223
00:15:02.830 --> 00:15:06.060
Sorry, Vivi. Y'know...

224
00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:07.410
I might be... in trouble.

225
00:15:07.410 --> 00:15:08.670
Nami! Hang in there!

226
00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:10.930
What the heck is that?!

227
00:15:12.690 --> 00:15:14.300
It's a cyclone!

228
00:15:14.300 --> 00:15:15.220
It's huge!

229
00:15:15.220 --> 00:15:18.380
W-Wait! That's the direction–

230
00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:21.360
That's the direction our ship
was just going!

231
00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:24.690
We would've hit it head-on
had we kept our original heading!

232
00:15:33.780 --> 00:15:37.330
Yikes! We just barely missed it!

233
00:15:38.060 --> 00:15:39.220
Incredible!

234
00:15:39.220 --> 00:15:43.080
Grand Line cyclones are said
to be impossible to predict!

235
00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:44.040
Yet, she...

236
00:15:45.120 --> 00:15:48.470
She doesn't predict weather
based on prevailing theory.

237
00:15:48.470 --> 00:15:51.510
It's almost as if she's detecting
the weather with her body!

238
00:15:51.510 --> 00:15:54.470
This navigator is one of a kind!

239
00:15:55.320 --> 00:15:57.430
Alright! Let's hurry, then!

240
00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:00.570
Let's go find us a doctor!

241
00:16:00.570 --> 00:16:01.640
Yeah!

242
00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:16.160
The Next Day

243
00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:24.520
What do we do, Vivi?!
Nami's fever won't break!

244
00:16:24.520 --> 00:16:27.130
Sanji! Karoo!
I asked you to stop freaking out!

245
00:16:34.420 --> 00:16:36.030
See any doctors?!

246
00:16:36.030 --> 00:16:37.640
You actually expect him to, moron?

247
00:16:42.110 --> 00:16:45.270
Hey, guys. Ever heard of people
who could stand on the ocean?

248
00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:47.870
Can people stand on the ocean?

249
00:16:47.870 --> 00:16:50.230
C'mon, Zoro.
Is this some kind of riddle?

250
00:16:50.950 --> 00:16:53.570
Then... what's that?

251
00:16:53.570 --> 00:16:55.270
What's what?

252
00:16:55.270 --> 00:16:56.410
Huh?

253
00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:20.390
Hi. It sure is chilly today.

254
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:23.310
Yeah! It is chilly today!

255
00:17:23.310 --> 00:17:26.600
Y-Yeah! Chilly, chilly!
Today's very chilly!

256
00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:28.150
Really?

257
00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:34.280
Increase buoyancy!

258
00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:35.280
Yes, sir!

259
00:17:41.940 --> 00:17:43.620
What's that?! A watermelon?!

260
00:17:43.620 --> 00:17:45.160
Why are we shaking?!

261
00:17:45.160 --> 00:17:49.880
Steady the rudder! If anything
happens to Nami, I'll gut you all!

262
00:17:53.670 --> 00:17:57.180
This thing can't actually be... a ship?!

263
00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:22.410
Crap! A p-pirate ship!

264
00:18:23.340 --> 00:18:24.290
S-So cool!

265
00:18:25.170 --> 00:18:27.000
Just when we're in a hurry...

266
00:18:30.270 --> 00:18:36.250
Surprised?! It's our jumbo
submersible raid ship, the Bliking!

267
00:18:40.890 --> 00:18:42.760
Vivi! Take over!

268
00:18:42.760 --> 00:18:43.510
Okay!

269
00:18:44.770 --> 00:18:46.560
Hey! What's going on?!

270
00:19:00.250 --> 00:19:02.870
So? What's going on?

271
00:19:03.250 --> 00:19:05.580
The ship's under attack.

272
00:19:10.390 --> 00:19:15.670
Well, I had figured as much
from the looks of things.

273
00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:21.930
Are you really pirates?
This can't be right.

274
00:19:21.930 --> 00:19:24.180
Is it just the four of you?

275
00:19:25.390 --> 00:19:31.320
"Tin Plate" Wapol
Bliking Pirates

276
00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:28.460
I find it hard to believe...

277
00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:31.310
that a pirate group would only have four people.

278
00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:38.990
What is that guy?!
He even ate the knife!

279
00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:42.360
Just watching hurts!

280
00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:46.390
Well, no matter.
First, a question for you.

281
00:19:47.480 --> 00:19:50.670
We want to go
to the Kingdom of Drum.

282
00:19:50.670 --> 00:19:53.230
Do you happen to have
an eternal pose or a log pose?

283
00:19:54.650 --> 00:19:59.170
Nope. Never even heard of the place.

284
00:19:59.170 --> 00:20:02.230
Hey, if that's everything,
then get outta here!

285
00:20:02.230 --> 00:20:03.860
We're in a hurry!

286
00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:06.440
We don't have time to mess with you!

287
00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:10.450
Don't rush life like that.

288
00:20:10.450 --> 00:20:12.380
So you don't have either one, oh well.

289
00:20:12.380 --> 00:20:15.150
In that case, I'll take
your treasure and your ship.

290
00:20:15.150 --> 00:20:16.020
What?!

291
00:20:16.020 --> 00:20:19.690
But first, I'm feeling a bit hungry!

292
00:20:24.780 --> 00:20:26.700
What is this guy?!

293
00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:28.500
Get your mouth off our ship!

294
00:20:28.500 --> 00:20:29.580
Hold it right there!

295
00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:31.600
The great Wapol is currently eating!

296
00:20:31.600 --> 00:20:32.410
Shut up!

297
00:20:32.410 --> 00:20:35.130
Damn that bastard! Fire!

298
00:20:36.660 --> 00:20:39.340
Should've done that from the start...

299
00:20:39.590 --> 00:20:41.800
Oh? We can have at 'em?

300
00:20:41.800 --> 00:20:43.760
No, wait! We can discuss this!

301
00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:52.390
Look what they started.

302
00:20:52.390 --> 00:20:54.690
They're fools rushing to their deaths!

303
00:20:54.690 --> 00:20:55.730
Gunfire?!

304
00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:59.730
Karoo! Watch Nami!
I'll be right back!

305
00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:04.650
Don't bite off
more than you can chew!

306
00:21:04.820 --> 00:21:05.910
Réception!

307
00:21:30.150 --> 00:21:31.220
All bark and no bite.

308
00:21:32.320 --> 00:21:33.930
W-Wapol, sir! These guys are...!

309
00:21:36.440 --> 00:21:37.670
Are you still eating it?!

310
00:21:37.670 --> 00:21:39.590
Say, this ship doesn't taste half bad.

311
00:21:39.590 --> 00:21:40.570
Hey, you!

312
00:21:40.570 --> 00:21:42.800
Fool! You're no match
for the great Wapol!

313
00:21:42.800 --> 00:21:45.450
His Munch-Munch Fruit power
will eat you whole!

314
00:21:45.450 --> 00:21:46.320
Luffy!

315
00:21:48.710 --> 00:21:49.490
Wh-What is this?!

316
00:21:50.260 --> 00:21:52.960
Oh, Vivi, is everything
okay with Nami?

317
00:21:52.960 --> 00:21:53.500
Huh?

318
00:21:57.240 --> 00:21:59.460
This guy's hard to chew on!

319
00:22:00.630 --> 00:22:02.670
Why, you!

320
00:22:03.710 --> 00:22:05.020
Go flying!

321
00:22:09.640 --> 00:22:11.520
Wapol...?

322
00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:17.310
Hey, this is really bad!
He sent the great Wapol flying!

323
00:22:17.310 --> 00:22:21.570
This is a disaster!
The great Wapol isn't able to swim!

324
00:22:21.570 --> 00:22:28.780
He will surely drown and perish in the sea
if he sinks before we can retrieve him!

325
00:22:29.030 --> 00:22:30.640
This isn't over, you!

326
00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:32.450
We'll make you pay for this!

327
00:22:32.450 --> 00:22:34.540
Remember us!

328
00:22:34.540 --> 00:22:36.560
You're gonna pay!

329
00:22:36.560 --> 00:22:41.030
Please, remember us! Please!

330
00:22:45.600 --> 00:22:49.350
J-Just now, what was all that?

331
00:22:49.350 --> 00:22:51.660
So, I guess his name is Wapol?

332
00:22:51.660 --> 00:22:54.370
Doesn't matter. Don't sweat it.

333
00:22:54.370 --> 00:22:56.020
He's a moron.

334
00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:57.810
Let's just forget about him.

335
00:23:05.250 --> 00:23:08.080
Where have I seen him before?

336
00:23:17.790 --> 00:23:22.450
Will her fever go down
if we dump water on her?

337
00:23:22.450 --> 00:23:23.700
You dumbass!

338
00:23:24.460 --> 00:23:27.460
This isn't good. The sun's
about to set for today, Vivi.

339
00:23:27.460 --> 00:23:29.280
Yes... You're right.

340
00:23:29.280 --> 00:23:31.670
Let's drop anchor somewhere.

341
00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:35.010
We can't sail at night
without Nami's navigation.

342
00:23:35.010 --> 00:23:36.560
True.

343
00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:07.960
Brr, it's cold...

344
00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:14.400
Almost a full moon, huh?

345
00:24:27.780 --> 00:24:30.120
Brr! Oh, crap, I fell asleep!

346
00:24:31.270 --> 00:24:32.990
You're up early, Usopp!

347
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:35.200
I can't just sit around doing nothing!

348
00:24:35.200 --> 00:24:38.620
We gotta get out of this jam
as quickly as possible!

349
00:24:38.930 --> 00:24:41.500
Yeah. Good point.

350
00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:52.970
Say, isn't this area
unusually calm and cold?

351
00:24:53.330 --> 00:24:56.570
Yeah, sudden, strange calms...

352
00:24:56.570 --> 00:25:00.970
I guess that's another
erratic quirk of the Grand Line.

353
00:25:00.970 --> 00:25:03.390
That's not necessarily the case.

354
00:25:03.690 --> 00:25:06.150
This is likely proof of a nearby island.

355
00:25:06.150 --> 00:25:08.860
Sanji, can you carefully
scan the horizon?

356
00:25:09.360 --> 00:25:10.360
Vivi?

357
00:25:11.630 --> 00:25:14.270
A winter island is nearby.
I'm certain of it.

358
00:25:14.270 --> 00:25:15.450
– Winter island?
– Ow!

359
00:25:16.120 --> 00:25:20.950
Climate-wise, the Grand Line
has four basic island types:

360
00:25:21.760 --> 00:25:26.150
Summer isles, spring isles,
autumn isles, and winter isles.

361
00:25:26.150 --> 00:25:29.600
In addition, each one generally
has four seasons of its own.

362
00:25:28.760 --> 00:25:40.690
Summery Summer            Wintery Winter
Summer Island Spring Island Autumn Island Winter Island

363
00:25:30.300 --> 00:25:35.060
On the Grand Line, you contend
with no fewer than sixteen seasons.

364
00:25:35.060 --> 00:25:40.680
There are summer island summers
and even winter island winters.

365
00:25:41.910 --> 00:25:47.060
Of course, there are many exceptions
and unknown climates.

366
00:25:47.060 --> 00:25:48.520
I get it.

367
00:25:48.520 --> 00:25:52.170
The Grand Line consists
of strings of various islands,

368
00:25:52.170 --> 00:25:56.480
and weather is adversely affected
on the seas between them.

369
00:25:56.480 --> 00:25:57.660
That's right.

370
00:25:57.660 --> 00:26:03.330
So when the weather stabilizes,
you're near an island.

371
00:26:03.830 --> 00:26:06.410
You're right! There it is!

372
00:26:09.990 --> 00:26:12.220
We found an island!

373
00:26:14.350 --> 00:26:15.550
An island?!

374
00:26:15.930 --> 00:26:18.380
Oh! An island! We found an island!

375
00:26:18.380 --> 00:26:22.640
Hey, Nami! Great news!
It's an island! You'll get better!

376
00:26:22.640 --> 00:26:25.130
There's an island! An island! Island!

377
00:26:25.130 --> 00:26:31.080
Island! Island! Island! Island!

378
00:26:31.080 --> 00:26:33.160
Just go look already. I'll watch her.
Island! Island!

379
00:26:38.280 --> 00:26:40.820
An island!

380
00:26:41.120 --> 00:26:45.120
White! So white! Has to be snow!
A snow island, huh?!

381
00:26:45.120 --> 00:26:49.440
Hey, Luffy! Just remember,
this isn't the time for adventure!

382
00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:51.290
It's a quick stop to find a doctor.

383
00:26:51.290 --> 00:26:53.810
Once Nami's looked at, we're gone!

384
00:26:53.810 --> 00:26:55.410
Hey! Hey, Luffy!

385
00:26:56.160 --> 00:26:59.510
Snow is so nice and white!

386
00:26:59.850 --> 00:27:01.440
It's no use. He's not listening.

387
00:27:01.440 --> 00:27:04.060
H-H-Hold on! Is this a good idea?!

388
00:27:04.060 --> 00:27:07.150
If there's snow, won't there
also be snow monsters?!

389
00:27:07.150 --> 00:27:10.060
And we don't know
if people live there! Oh, no!

390
00:27:10.060 --> 00:27:12.440
My chronic can't-get-on-this-island disease!

391
00:27:12.440 --> 00:27:16.240
Snow! I love snow! It's white!

392
00:27:16.240 --> 00:27:18.440
Guess I'll prep us for landfall.

393
00:27:46.480 --> 00:27:49.840
All this snow! It's pure happiness!

394
00:27:50.510 --> 00:27:53.440
This is really something.
What's with those mountains?

395
00:27:54.410 --> 00:27:57.830
Say, Luffy. Aren't you cold,
dressed like that?

396
00:27:57.830 --> 00:28:00.210
It's minus 10 degrees right now!

397
00:28:00.210 --> 00:28:02.450
That's when bears
get ready to hibernate!

398
00:28:02.870 --> 00:28:04.220
Huh? Oh.

399
00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:06.580
So cold!

400
00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:08.660
Took you long enough!

401
00:28:13.210 --> 00:28:15.800
It's a waterfall of melted snow.

402
00:28:15.800 --> 00:28:17.810
We may be able to dock here.

403
00:28:18.340 --> 00:28:21.690
So, who's going doctor hunting?

404
00:28:21.690 --> 00:28:22.970
Actually, you see any people?

405
00:28:23.540 --> 00:28:24.300
I'm going!

406
00:28:24.300 --> 00:28:25.220
So am I!

407
00:28:25.220 --> 00:28:26.600
Okay! Have fun!

408
00:28:26.600 --> 00:28:28.810
That's far enough, pirates!

409
00:28:43.780 --> 00:28:46.290
Hey. I found people.

410
00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:49.700
But... they don't seem too friendly.

411
00:28:51.180 --> 00:28:53.160
Attention, pirates!

412
00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:56.500
Turn around and leave
this place immediately!

413
00:28:56.500 --> 00:28:58.980
We came to find a doctor!

414
00:28:58.980 --> 00:29:00.470
There's a sick person on board!

415
00:29:00.470 --> 00:29:03.680
That's a dirty trick,
you pirate bastards!

416
00:29:04.070 --> 00:29:08.420
On our island, any and all
pirates are barred entry!

417
00:29:08.420 --> 00:29:12.890
Raise anchor and leave,
or we'll blow your ship to smithereens!

418
00:29:14.320 --> 00:29:17.810
They really hate our guts.
And we've only just met.

419
00:29:17.810 --> 00:29:19.020
Less talking!

420
00:29:19.440 --> 00:29:20.410
They're shooting!

421
00:29:20.410 --> 00:29:21.900
You did not just do that!

422
00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:23.190
– No, Sanji!
– Bastard!

423
00:29:34.450 --> 00:29:35.900
Vivi!
